title: Six Teens Rescued After Falling Through Ice in Central Park, Police Say
text:
Six Teens Rescued After Falling Through Ice in Central Park, Police Say By Alexandra Leon | February 20, 2017 7:06pm View Full Caption Twitter/@FDNY 
MIDTOWN â€” At least six teens were rescued after falling through ice in a Central Park pond, officials said. 
The teens, who are between 15 and 16, fell into the water near Sixth Avenue and Central Park South just before 6 p.m., according to the FDNY and the NYPD. 
Divers were still searching for other possible victims at 7 p.m., the FDNY said. 
The teens were treated for hypothermia, according to the New York Daily News . 
It wasn't immediately clear how they fell in the water.
